No fewer than 197,269 children have been vaccinated against measles in the first phase of the immunisation programme in Kwara. Dr Iyabode Ajibola, the Communication for Development Consultant in the state, disclosed this to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Sunday in Ilorin. NAN reports that the first phase, which began early this month, covered eight local government areas. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.